Editor | Xiao Zhu

1

At 6 pm on the third day of the Lunar New Year, wan-ou has been working in Zhejiang Province Health Commission for 36 hours, only a meal.

She's the product manager for the stapler team. On the evening of the first day of the Lunar New Year, they received a notification from the Health Commission of Zhejiang Province that they wanted to set up a new public service and management platform for pneumonia, hoping that the nail team could provide technical support.

At that time, the team only in the gull is still in Hangzhou, only she can to Zhejiang Province health commission to do this thing.

University, Wan Gull learned clinical medicine, has been in the hospital internship and work. This was the second time she had experienced a break from her old life after coming to the nail team.

The last time was in the first half of 2019, when she went on a three month business trip to Quzhou, Zhejiang Province. She wanted to see if she could build on the platform and do something for doctors at the grassroots level.

Wan Gull in the city of Hangzhou Large Hospital work experience, which is completely different from the work experience of primary-level doctors. In big cities and hospitals, residents often come to the doctor on their own initiative, often for only a few minutes. At the grassroots level, it is usually the doctor who visits the patient's home. "doctors at the grassroots level have a lot of business to do, such as making spreadsheets, going on and on about health education and education. "

In Quzhou's mountainous terrain, many doctors spend hours each day climbing mountains to reach their patients'homes. Some residents of the condition is really bad, make Wan Gull impression is a family lost children, his wife is cerebral palsy patients, Wan Gull and the doctor into the house, the male host served a drink to serve. He took out the most precious thing. "

Before long, nail family doctor products came on the line, and the value of each individual primary care worker was put even greater through the platform.

New Crown Epidemic Current, nail and Zhejiang Health Committee Cooperation Project, also has the same significance. It's a platform for the public and for the health care community. Residents can complete online notification of the outbreak, experience medical observation services, search for patients on the same trip, and online intelligent consultation.

Before the program is launched, each doctor will have to manage dozens of "grids, " and in some hard-hit areas, one may have dozens or even hundreds of suspected patients or close contacts. The doctor needs to come in, find these people, take their temperature one by one. Some people don't want to open the door, others may cause cross-infection. A trip to the field means more masks and other medical supplies. After the area is accounted for, the doctors manually enter the results.

In Quzhou, the experience of the impact of the Wan Gull. When she received the urgent task from the Health Protection Commission, she already had a deep understanding of the working conditions of front-line workers, especially the doctors at the grassroots level. "In a short time, we can know what the working conditions of the medical workers at the grassroots level will be, how to deal with the residents. It's basically just a simple conversation, and I have a picture of it. And then you do this product, and the whole process is very fast. "

The digital epidemic prevention system is a platform for epidemic prevention launched in cooperation with local governments by the teams of Nail, Alibaba Cloud, Alipay, Dharma House, government nail, etc. . On the platform, residents can make on-line consultation, health care workers can also count fevers and suspected cases online.

It's just that it's never easy for a new product to take on a task, come up with an idea, go through a few rounds of trial and error, and finally go live. In order to meet the requirements of customization in a special period, "it is very difficult to provide some customized products and practices in a very short time. ". "wan-ou said.

She was the first night of the Lunar New Year's Day received a phone call, thought the first morning of the second day of the Lunar New Year was just to Zhejiang Health Commission for a brief meeting, did not expect to stay in that building for several days. The only impression she had of the meal was that the man at the dining-room window was "rather fierce" , perhaps because, in times of crisis, even the rules of the dining-room had been tightened, and a certificate was required for bringing an extra meal. "But how was the meal? I don't really remember. "

At present, the digital epidemic prevention system has covered 28 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions. Wan Feel and health care commission customers bred a feeling, between them the original sense of distance and boundaries, after the intensive day and night together, into a feeling of comrade-in-arms, "we seem to really be friends. ". "

She thought it was a battle, and she was on the front lines.

Wan Yuen Interviewee

2

Kotate, a high school senior in Xichuan County, Henan Province, had just finished lunch at 12:00 noon on the third day of the same year. It's one of the few free times in his day. He got a phone call.

Like most high school seniors, it was a tough year, starting at 6 a.m. and going to bed at 10 p.m. , and Kotate was one of many students who wanted to change their lives by studying.

Since the provinces have adjusted the level of major public health emergencies to level one, homeschooling has become a necessity for students. In particular, will face the college entrance examination of the senior three students, the last few months of sprint, often directly determine the fate of things.

KOTATE's grades are in the top three in his school, and his target is Zhejiang University. However, the study under the epidemic needs the support of hardware. He is already in the big province of Gaokao, and the competition is fierce. Now he seems to have opened a more difficult mode. His home has no net, and the traffic is expensive. He called his neighbors, and use the Internet next door for lectures. When the signal's bad, he has to climb up to the roof and crash into the net. In early spring in Central Plain, a silent figure climbs onto the roof to fulfill his dream of studying.

The call came from Shōni, who had been paying particular attention to Henan Province. In Henan, a province with 14 poor counties, "if there was no epidemic, I would have been able to take off my hat by now. "He asked Unicom's partners to help pay attention to the 14 counties, children attending online classes may encounter any difficulties? Does the hardware pass muster? Will Wi-fi and broadband be enough? Shall I wire the net? Don't you have a cell phone at home?

It's just, a situation like this can't be solved online. On the other end of the line, "very lightly" , "what kind of kid is this? What kind of a scene is this? "The nail-biter was still wondering.

After hanging up the phone, he immediately contacted Li Yang of China Unicom, which is in charge of promoting Xichuan County's infrastructure. After some thought, Li Yang set off for the boy's house.

It was a rental house for reading, a bungalow, a room. The most things in the room are books, the door is a simple stove, the classroom desk is a common narrow desk, the surface of the peeling marks, hanging above the family's clean clothes.

The boy's parents work in the supermarket, although the income is not high, but it is not the most difficult family in the local.

And then I went back to my original assumption that there might be some people who don't have the hardware? This is not to say that poor (to what extent) , but that at this stage, we still have a lot of digital breakthrough, many ways of thinking to break. "said Shōni the nail.

Concerned about minimizing the loss of not being able to return to school, the team began by installing hardware infrastructure at schools in Henan and Yunnan from the third day of the year, such as cable and scaffolding for live broadcasting. When classes can not be resumed, the hardware is a guarantee for teachers to teach online. At the very least, make sure the teacher finds the student, and the student finds the teacher.

Online teaching, a last-resort response to the epidemic, could be an opportunity for change. Through the Internet and screens, children in mountainous areas can also see the live lectures of excellent teachers in big cities. Some of the inherent differences with the diaphragm can be broken down gradually.

Inside view of Kotate's home

3

At six or seven in the morning, before most people wake up, it's the busiest time for the nail workers.

The morning was the most intense for the entire technical team. 8:00,9:00,10:00, three of the highest traffic on the hour. Companies hold morning meetings and students take online classes, usually from these nodes, creating hours of peak traffic that doesn't peak until 12 noon.

It's a test of technology and servers. The CTO of nail described the difficulty of the test in terms of analogy: The 8 am and 9 am rush hour for nail was like the pressure of watching dozens of World Cup finals in an hour.

What the team needs to do is anticipate the potential traffic before 8:00 and use the Alibaba Cloud servers to ensure that the software does not crash or jam when a large number of users arrive at the same time. As if it were a pre-exam review and guess.

On March 3rd it added 10,000, on April 4th it added another 10,000, and on December 12th it added 100,000 cloud servers through Alibaba Cloud.

Yang Xu is Alibaba Cloud's technical director for server extensions. He said Alibaba Cloud's support for nail enlargement could be likened to building a Vulcan Mountain Hospital: Normally it would take three or four months to build a house, first laying the foundation, then building the skeleton, then laying the cement. But in times of crisis, deadlines are compressed.

Yang Xu remembers a night when a batch of servers had to be sent from Shenzhen, which was a dozen degrees Celsius, to Zhangbei, which was snowing hard. Huge servers sit overnight in dedicated trucks that need to be disinfected every time they pass a checkpoint. He's in a work group that's broadcasting live. Everybody cares. Where's the truck now? What's the ETA on that?

Alibaba Cloud expands the server in transit to source interviewees

The feed went live for four hours, and in the early hours of the morning, the servers were in place in Zhangbei. People watching live as they work are relieved.

At this point, only a few hours before the morning rush hour, the technical staff in the rear must hurry to expand capacity. It's like a marathon relay. No one dares to delay the progress, everyone is thinking about how to run faster, to leave more time for the next stick.

They've got the resources in place in the shortest amount of time, and then they're going to build the house.

This House, built on a cloud, was built using a method similar to 3D printing. Rapid modeling, automated processes, standardized delivery. "It's like a model room. "He said.

After the big test starts at 8:00, we can basically decide which areas should be downgraded and which areas should be expanded. This means that the test passed, hung up the heart of the day can be put on hold.

Every day is a little cycle, every week a great cycle -- until 8:00 am next Monday, another test.

On duty in the morning, a millet table is always full of screens: two desktop screens, a laptop, a tablet, three mobile phones. The devices do their job -- as if the tablet were looking at a water table, with two phones connected to different video conferencing, and one to answer calls, with separate battle group chats.

Similar to the abrupt flow curve, the workload of team members has also risen steeply in just a few days.

"sometimes, when we have a party in the evening, we open it and hear the sound of hoo-hoo. Some students lie down on their desks and go to sleep and play, more than once or twice. "said ICHIGO, not sounding critical.

Since they couldn't get back to work offline, the people on the team had to communicate via videoconference.

Wan Gull also remember, in her first step into the command room of the Health Commission in Zhejiang Province, the big screen is holding a video conference. She was embarrassed and said, "we didn't use much before. The client used it better than we did. ".

At first, working via video chat was a little weird. The instant a video call is connected, colleagues'faces appear on the screen, some unwashed, some still wearing pajamas. A lot of people's first instinct is to turn off the cameras. A grain of salt noticed the problem. Later, they launched the beauty feature, and the number of people willing to turn on the camera significantly increased. At this point, a grain can not help but want to laugh.

Later, we gradually formed a tacit understanding. Before the session begins, they dress as if it were a ritual, then clear out their backgrounds in an attempt to create a quiet workspace in a variety of settings. Occasionally, however, there are special circumstances. Many people in the video conference room to see the children in the home coquetry colleagues, parents in the shouting to eat, there are 5-year-old Samoyed. One of my colleagues was stuck in his hometown, and every morning at 7:30 a.m. , the family rooster would crow on time.

200 million users, 50 million students, 10 million businesses. This is February 25, Nail 5.0 new product meeting, CEO Chen Hang mentioned the number. When large crowds gather in the clouds, everyone can push and accomplish more through the platform.

If, many years later, he wanted to recall the overlapping days and days, the days became thick for more than a month, he thought, what he would remember most was that each morning, nail and Ali Yun's two teams would pull him into a video conference at the same time, start the day with an "Early Watch" inspection. In-house teams, "Early Watch" is a time-honored tradition. The person on duty each day acts like a sentry on patrol, checking for possible problems early. The conference room was as noisy as ever, across the distance, and somewhere out of sight on the other side of the screen, at 7:30, a rooster crowed.
